# CODEOWNERS -- declared review ownership for trust-critical areas.
#
# This file names the account responsible for reviewing changes to the paths
# below. It does NOT by itself require review, and it does NOT establish
# independent review: on a solo-maintained project the owner and the author are
# often the same person, so this does not close the Scorecard Code-Review check.
# Code-owner review is only enforced once branch protection is configured (a
# repository setting, not this file) to require it.
#
# Owning `.github/workflows/` and this CODEOWNERS file keeps the CI, release, and
# ownership controls themselves inside the declared critical surface, so they
# cannot be changed without routing to the designated owner once enforcement is
# enabled.

/.github/CODEOWNERS                         @madeinplutofabio
/.github/workflows/                         @madeinplutofabio
/SECURITY.md                                @madeinplutofabio
/THREAT_MODEL.md                            @madeinplutofabio
/packages/git/                              @madeinplutofabio
/packages/session-format/                   @madeinplutofabio
/packages/cli-commands/**/*pty*             @madeinplutofabio
/scripts/release-*                          @madeinplutofabio
